<subSubSection id="1CBEC0C7FFD6FFCDFF47F966FE39F802" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="541B934CFFD6FFCDFF47F966FCAEF912" blockId="25.[151,1436,746,1932]" box="[198,859,1666,1692]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="66D04F5EFFD6FFCDFF47F966FED7F912" bold="true" box="[198,290,1666,1692]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Biology</emphasis>
. Collected under 
<taxonomicName id="93A4E8CFFFD6FFCDFE72F967FD35F912" box="[499,704,1667,1692]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Pistacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lentiscus">
<emphasis id="66D04F5EFFD6FFCDFE72F967FD35F912" box="[499,704,1667,1692]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pistacia lentiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. in woods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="541B934CFFD6FFCDFF47F94EFE39F802" blockId="25.[151,1436,746,1932]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="66D04F5EFFD6FFCDFF47F94EFEF9F94A" bold="true" box="[198,268,1706,1732]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Notes</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="93A4E8CFFFD6FFCDFE9BF94FFE19F94A" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1908" box="[282,492,1707,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Peritelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inviridis">
<emphasis id="66D04F5EFFD6FFCDFE9BF94FFE19F94A" box="[282,492,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Peritelus inviridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered by 
<bibRefCitation id="3035EEBDFFD6FFCDFD53F94EFC22F94A" author="Solari, A. &amp; Solari, F." box="[722,983,1706,1732]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="54 - 60" refId="ref47251" refString="Solari, A. &amp; Solari, F. (1922) Alcune note sui Peritelus e specialmente su quelli appartenenti al sottogenere Homorhythmus Bedel. Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 54 (4), 54 - 60." type="journal article" year="1922">Solari &amp; Solari (1922)</bibRefCitation>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="93A4E8CFFFD6FFCDFB25F94FFEE6F962" authority="Schaufuss, 1882" authorityName="Schaufuss" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Peritelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuicornis">
<emphasis id="66D04F5EFFD6FFCDFB25F94FFAB1F94A" box="[1188,1348,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. tenuicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3035EEBDFFD6FFCDFACAF94EFEE6F962" author="Schaufuss, L. W." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="527 - 552" refId="ref46900" refString="Schaufuss, L. W. (1882) Zoologische Ergebnisse von Excursionen auf den Balearen. III (Addenda und Fortsetzung). Numquam Otiosus, 3, 527 - 552." type="journal article" year="1882">Schaufuss, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the elytral profile “ 
<emphasis id="66D04F5EFFD6FFCDFDF8F937FB84F962" box="[633,1137,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">ex humeris ad posticam partem angustatis</emphasis>
” — according to Schaufuss’ description —, a character in fact shared by different 
<taxonomicName id="93A4E8CFFFD6FFCDFCEAF91EFC2FF89A" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1863" box="[875,986,1786,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Peritelini">Peritelini</taxonomicName>
. Examination of Pic’s 
<typeStatus id="8B1F2DEEFFD6FFCDFB71F91EFAD7F89A" box="[1264,1314,1786,1812]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
specimen revealed that 
<taxonomicName id="93A4E8CFFFD6FFCDFEB4F8C7FE23F8B2" authorityName="Schaufuss" authorityYear="1882" box="[309,470,1827,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Peritelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuicornis">
<emphasis id="66D04F5EFFD6FFCDFEB4F8C7FE23F8B2" box="[309,470,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. tenuicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is actually easy to distiguish, apart from the characters in the key also by the indicated longitudinal keel on the pronotum, the suberect elytral setae and the pre-apical region of aedeagus being bent down and broadened.
</paragraph>
